With a great flourish you swing your arms out, and the morning light seeps through the buildings behind you, spreading a gentle warmth across your back.
Beside you, Adi chuckles at your antics as she picks up the small satchel on her feet.
wiks: Ah, freedom!
adi: We're literally less than a few hours away from home, Wiks. Calm down.
wiks: Make me.
Adi rolls her eyes at you, but you can see the corner of her mouth curling up to a smile.
adi: Well, while [i]you[/i] do that, I'm going to go around, look for a meal that's not on top of a moving boat.
wiks: I'll be right behind you.
