label outro_pre_camera
if Events.get_current_pov() == Events.POV_Character.WIKS:
	Time passes as you wander around, finally able to drink in the sights now that you aren't in exploration duty.
	You find Adi near the water, her hands absentmindedly playing with the camera she's holding.
	She doesn't hear you.
	wiks: Hey Adi, admiring the view?
	She shakes her head.
	adi: Just... thinking.
	adi: Is there a problem?
	wiks: Oh, I was thinking that we've had quite the time here, so let's take a picture now before we head out.
	adi: Oh... Oh! I almost forgot. Here.
	She hands you the camera.
	adi: I'll trust your scouting eyes with right angles, Wiks.
if Events.get_current_pov() == Events.POV_Character.ADI:
	Time passes as you explore the place,  the sights refreshing memories you've forgotten.
	Eventually, you head back to where you started, legs taking you to Wiks, his height and gear making him stand out in the streets.
	He leans against the side of the big tree when you approach him, camera in your hand.
	wiks: What’s up? Just catching my breath.
	You hold out the camera.
	adi: I think we’ve checked the place out pretty well. Wanna take a picture for [i]tita[/i]?
	He beams at you, as he gives an enthusiastic thumbs up.
	wiks: Sure thing! As our resident artist, I’ll let your eye guide the camera.
	You just roll your eyes at him as you chuckle and bring the viewfinder up.
jump end
label outro_post_camera
Time passes.
adi: So where are we going next?
The two of you are sitting in a tree stump next to the boat rental. To no one's surprise, the Singer was as good as her word. The moment you said her name, they merely asked for a destination and immediately set to work. Behind you, you can hear someone barking orders.
wiks: Cubo. Good halfway point to practically everywhere, since it's a transport hub. From there, we can go to either…
adi: Hm, any chance we can go to those skyscrapers you told me about before? The ones down south?
adi: I've always wanted to check it out.
wiks: Sure, why not? It's a bit far from Cubo, but we should be able to reach it just before sundown. It's close to the coast though, so we might need to be careful of high tides.
adi: Will that be a problem?
wiks: We don't typically worry about it here, but closer to the shore, the waters rise fast. Doesn't take long entire streets to vanish.
Adi thinks for a moment.
adi: I'll let you decide.
The two of you gather your things in silence as the boatman approaches, and with him, the next leg of your journey.
